*like to do long quests and be proud of completing it<br>
*people who do not want to raid hardcore or be in high level guilds to get similar stuff <br>
*people in small guilds who like to help each others<br>
*people without tons of play times who like to get decent stuff on their own or with only a bit help (only the end quest encounters usually need a raid force)<br>
*roleplay<br>
<br>
I think they should leave the Kunark epics as they are at the moment, BUT maybe introduce a new form of 'epics', maybe Epic part II, with or without you having to have the old epic in your possesion.<br>
Maybe introduce new quests that lead to good weapons/items, again long quests that need a lot of running, fighting, exploring, patience and determination, but a lot harder to get based on level of the monsters you have to fight and the zones you have to visit. <br>
Kunark epics are level 50+ i think, make a new form of epic stuff level 60+, either with PoP content or one of the upcomming expansions. Do not change current epics. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img.villagephotos.com/p/2003-6/191888/Peq2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
